# Kendo UI Fluent Patterns

## Always Use VDC Wrappers in Mockups

<!-- Use VDC wrapper -->
<vdc-button variant="primary">Save</vdc-button>
<vdc-grid [data]="items"></vdc-grid>

<!-- Don't use raw Kendo directly in mockups -->

## VDC Wrapper Pattern

@Component({
  selector: 'vdc-button',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [ButtonsModule],
  template: <button kendoButton [themeColor]="themeColor"><ng-content></ng-content></button>
})
export class VdcButtonComponent {
  @Input() variant: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'destructive' = 'primary';
}

## Tailwind + Kendo Coexistence

- Use Tailwind for layout (flex, grid, spacing, positioning)
- Use Kendo theme for component styling (colors, borders, shadows)
- Override Kendo only via _kendo-fluent-overrides.scss

<!-- Layout with Tailwind, component is Kendo -->
<div class="flex gap-4 p-6">
  <vdc-dropdown [data]="options"></vdc-dropdown>
  <vdc-button variant="primary">Apply</vdc-button>
</div>
